* Of this flickering candle

251
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:12,277
* Illuminate the night
the way your spirit

252
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:23,430
* Illuminates my soul

253
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,396
* Papa...

254
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:30,835
* Can you hear me?

255
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,668
* Papa, can you see me?

256
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:42,678
* Papa, can you find me in the night?

257
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:44,751
* Papa, are you near me?

258
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:46,956
* Papa, can you hear me?

259
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:53,115
* Papa, can you help me
not be frightened?

260
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,512
* Looking at the skies

261
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,750
* I seem to see a million eyes

262
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:03,233
* Which ones are yours?

263
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:06,517
* Where are you now that yesterday
has waved goodbye

264
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:09,717
* And closed its doors?

265
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:13,395
* The night is so much darker

266
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:16,790
* The wind is so much colder

267
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,838
* The world I see is so much bigger

268
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:23,993
* Now that I'm alone

269
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:27,709
* Papa, please forgive me

270
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,268
* Try to understand me

271
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:35,070
* Papa, don't you know I had no choice?

272
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,754
* Can you hear me praying

273
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:40,070
* Anything I'm saying

274
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:45,792
* Even though the night
is filled with voices?

275
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:48,235
* I remember everything you taught me

276
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:55,351
* Every book I've ever read

277
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:57,396
* Can all the words in all the books

278
00:21:57,480 --> 00:22:01,439
* Help me to face what lies ahead?

279
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,149
* The trees are so much taller

280
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:08,755
* And I feel so much smaller

281
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,308
* The moon is twice as lonely

282
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:16,679
* And the stars are half as bright

283
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:22,955
* Papa, how I Love you

284
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:27,873
* Papa, how I need you

285
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:31,999
* Papa, how I miss you

286
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:53,189
* Kissing me good night *

287
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:09,472
If I am not for myself, who will be for me?

288
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:13,792
(Lowers pitch) Who will be for me?
(Coughs)

289
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,711
Who will be for me?

290
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:19,110
If I am for myself alone, who am I?
(Lower) Who am I?

291
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:22,396
And if not now...

292
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:25,438
- (Horse neighing in distance)
- . . when?

293
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,397
(Yentl) Wait!

294
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:11,880
(Child shouting)

295
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:28,390
- (Lively chatter)
- (Man) Innkeeper, more soup!

296
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,995
(Chatter continues, men singing)

297
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:36,959
(Man) Did you hear that?
(2nd man) Yes. I hear, I hear.

298
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:39,349
(Singing continues)

299
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,396
(Man) Who's throwing that?

300
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:46,188
Don't throw that. I told you not to.

301
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:49,352
- Watch out!
- (Man) Lithuania, Poland, same thing.

302
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:54,230
A school is a school. It's only the rabbis
that are different. The girls...

303
00:24:56,760 --> 00:25:00,469
- Why would the Talmud repeat itself?
- It's an improper translation.

304
00:25:00,560 --> 00:25:04,075
- Even if they contradict each other?
- Avigdor, what do you think?

305
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:07,835
The Talmud recognizes
Life is filled with contradiction.

306
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,150
- You see? He agrees.
- Your move.

307
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:16,756
- Ah!
- What?

308
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:19,673
- Nothing, sorry.
- No, go on.

309
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:24,594
It's just that, erm, if you move your castle

310
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:27,035
- to queen 7...
- Yes?

311
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:29,796
His knight is pinned. That's all.

312
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,910
You don't know what you're talking about.

313
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,956
No. Sorry.

314
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:39,795
(Youth) Stop yelling at me, Papa.
(Man) I'm not yelling!

315
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:44,559
Checkmate.

316
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:49,833
The Long diagonal. Who knew?

317
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:52,150
You should’ve listened to him.

318
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:54,629
Chaim, catch!

319
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:57,996
- You want a bite?
- No, thank you.

320
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:01,516
- Don't play.
- Hey, you. You.

321
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:03,875
- Sit down.
- Why?

322
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,956
Because I said so.

323
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:13,035
Five kopecks if you win.
Pay me one if you lose.

324
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,076
What do I have to do?

325
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:17,230
Whoever forces
the other's hand down wins.

326
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,709
- No, thanks.
- Ready? Go!

327
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:21,756
(Grunts)

328
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:25,992
Wasn't it Rabbi Akiva who said,
''The true strength of a man... ''

329
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:28,275
One kopeck.

330
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:31,989
''. . Lies in his ability to stretch
the narrowest mind''? Thank you.

331
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:36,153
You're welcome.
Now you can stretch my mind again.

332
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,558
Go.

333
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:41,108
I think Rabbi Akiva also said...

334
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,599
Two kopecks.

335
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:46,309
- I thought it was one.
- Mm. But I beat you I twice.

336
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,277
Oh.

337
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:51,156
Give him back his money.

338
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,471
- Why?
- Because I said so.

339
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:56,312
Because you said so.

340
00:26:57,840 --> 00:27:01,958
I'll see you Later when your beard
starts to grow. Mama's boy.

341
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:06,559
- No, it wasn't, since you ask.
- Hm?

342
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:09,677
Rabbi Akiva. ''The narrowest mind. ''

343
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:12,832
Oh. Er, was it Rabbi Eliezer?

344
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,876
No, Rabbi Israel Salanter.

345
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:17,076
Rabbi Israel Salanter.

346
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:19,390
My brother didn't have one either.

347
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,232
What?

348
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,636
- Are you hungry?
- A Little.

349
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:27,632
- Help yourself.
- Yes, please.

350
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,756
Which yeshiva are you going to?

351
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:33,549
I haven't decided. Someplace quiet.

352
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:35,232
A quiet yeshiva?

353
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:37,993
- Bechev's the best.
- (Man) Well, the nearest.

354
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:39,638
That's where we study.

355
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:42,598
Well, I just count the days till I go home.

356
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:45,672
His parents count
the days until he goes back.

357
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:49,548
Our rabbi's a genius.
Rabbi Zalman? Maybe you've heard of him.

358
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:51,392
I think so.

359
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:53,516
In one answer, he settles ten questions.

360
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,716
Papa had 10 questions for every answer.

361
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,199
Had?

362
00:27:57,280 --> 00:28:00,352
He died eight days ago,
may he rest in peace.

363
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,589
You're in mourning too.

364
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,636
My brother.

365
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:10,190
Almost a month now. May he rest in peace.

366
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,956
I'm Shimmele, by the way.

367
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,076
- Oh.
- (Both) Hello.

368
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:21,033
- And you?
- What?

369
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:23,076
What's your name?

370
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:26,232
- My name?
- Name.

371
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,074
Um...

372
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:36,675
Anshel. That's it.
That's my name. My name is Anshel.

373
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,955
Good. You know your own name.

374
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,996
You're as good a scholar as I am.

375
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:43,355
- This is Avigdor.
- I know.

376
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,789
- I mean, hello.
- (Man) Boys!

377
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:52,352
Wagons to the north and west leaving now.
And now means now!

378
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,317
Goodbye.

379
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,356
Anshel.

380
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,715
(Lively chatter)

381
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:02,516
(Chicken clucking)

382
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:10,078
Anshel!

383
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:12,833
Hey, are you deaf? Anshel!

384
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,672
Anshel. Yes?

385
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:16,830
There's room if you're still undecided.

386
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,717
I just decided.

387
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:22,598
(* Men singing and clapping)

388
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:29,189
* He tells him there's a fisherman
who's got the strongest rod

389
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:31,316
* The cod he catches are so big

390
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:33,038
* And when they see
his cod they scream! *

391
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:35,839
- Where you from, Anshel?
- Erm...

392
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:38,992
A Little village
you've never heard of. Yanev.

393
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:42,595
Yanev? I have relatives in Yanev.
A third cousin.

394
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,636
- We moved.
- What?

395
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:46,676
(Yentl) Years ago.

396
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:49,638
- You have relatives in Riga?
- Riga?

397
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:53,519
- No.
- Now we live in Riga.

398
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:56,031
Oh.

399
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:04,630
(Avigdor) Were you close?
(Yentl) He was my father and teacher.

400
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:08,110
(Avigdor) What more could you ask?
(Yentl) What about your brother?

401
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:10,156
- We were brothers.
- Older? Younger?

402
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,674
- Younger, about your age.
- What happened?

403
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:14,671
Pneumonia.

404
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:16,591
Sorry.

405
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,716
Would you Like to discuss
a page of Talmud?

406
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,075
- Oh, no, not Talmud.
- Which?

407
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:29,756
- Whatever you're reading.
- I'll state the premise. You dispute it.

408
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:39,115
- When does day become night?
- (Yentl) Sundown.

409
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:42,237
- (Avigdor) When is sundown?
- When you see three stars.

410
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,276
Not precise enough. When's dusk?

411
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:46,828
- When the light's no longer blue.
- That's twilight.

412
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:51,277
- Twilight is when objects are silhouettes.
- Be quiet for five minutes!

413
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:54,397
There's Bechev! We're home!

414
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:56,710
(Lively chatter)

415
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,796
(Yentl) How do I get into this yeshiva?

416
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:09,635
(Avigdor) Rabbi Zalman tests you on what
you know or what you think you know.

417
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:12,075
(Yentl) Can I live at this Yeshiva?

418
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:17,314
(Avigdor) No, but you'll find lodgings.
There may be a room where I stay.

419
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:20,836
(Man) I'm starving.
(2nd man) You're always starving.

420
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:24,555
- (Yentl) Wait for me!
- You walk too slow.

421
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:27,791
- (Yentl) You walk too fast.
- The synagogue's to the left,

422
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:30,633
the yeshiva's straight ahead,
I live around the corner.

423
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:33,598
- (Knock on door)
- Who is it?

424
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:36,592
- (Avigdor) It's me.
- Avigdor?

425
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,989
How many other boyfriends do you have?

426
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,150
I'm so glad you're back!

427
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:43,993
- (Laughs) Are you all right?
- Yes, yes.

428
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:46,036
When you see Hadass you’ll feel better.

429
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:48,395
Who wants other girls when I've got you?

430
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:52,155
- Shame! A wicked tongue.
- I want you to meet my friend, Anshel.

431
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:55,391
- Anshel, Mrs Jacobs.
- Good evening.

432
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,909
- Anshel?
- Do you have a room for him?

433
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,560
Oh, I'm sorry, dear, not tonight.

434
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:04,598
My niece is here,
but she leaves tomorrow.

435
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:08,434
- All right, he can share my bed.
- (Yentl) No, I can't.

436
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:10,909
Why not?

437
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,150
- I don't want to impose.
- Don't be silly.

438
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:16,755
- I'm a restless sleeper.
- That's all right. I snore.

439
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:18,796
(Avigdor) Come on.

440
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,632
Young.

441
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,834
Anshel, will you put out the lamp?

442
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:38,397
I can't. I'm being tested
by the rabbi tomorrow.

443
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:42,359
So? You're going to Learn the entire
Talmud by heart overnight?

444
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,590
All 2, 555 pages?

445
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:47,319
- You're tired, you sleep.
- I'm exhausted.

446
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:51,075
I've been in the wagon all day,
all I want to do is sleep.

447
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:53,230
Get in bed.

448
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,436
- Would you Like to talk a Little?
- Bed.

449
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:59,069
- Why don't I just...
- Get in bed.

450
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:15,756
So, er...

451
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:19,360
- Who's Hadass?
- Hm?

452
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:23,393
- Mrs Jacobs mentioned...
- For God's sake!

453
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:26,597
Sorry. It doesn't matter.
Go back to sleep.

454
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:29,396
The girl I'm engaged to.

455
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:31,638
Oh.

456
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,836
- (Thud)
- Sorry.

457
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:37,718
- Oh, it's your suitcase.
- (Sighs)

458
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:45,999
Is she, er, pretty, this Hadass?

459
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,433
No.

460
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:49,431
Beautiful.

461
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:56,951
What color hair does she have?

462
00:33:57,040 --> 00:34:00,271
I dine at her house every Tuesday.
I'll take you.

463
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:03,119
Thank you.

464
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,156
(Avigdor sighs)

465
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:10,275
- Red.
- Hm. Red, huh?

466
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:13,033
- Will you get into bed?
- Sure.

467
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:34,996
You’ll fall off the edge.

468
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:39,395
I always sleep Like this.

469
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:41,789
- Why?
- Why?

470
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,956
I... I think it's written.

471
00:34:46,640 --> 00:34:47,993
What is?

472
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:51,470
Two bachelors in the same bed
must lie back to back.

473
00:34:52,640 --> 00:34:54,392
- Really?
- Really.

474
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:56,436
So turn over, please.

475
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:10,118
Why'd you have to talk about Hadass?

476
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,316
Now I'll never get to sleep.

477
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,753
Why not?

478
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:16,957
Don't you ever think sinful thoughts?

479
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:18,712
- No.
- No?

480
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,836
- Yes!
- Don't be so nervous.

481
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,876
Why should I be nervous?

482
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:27,119
You're being tested
by the rabbi tomorrow.

483
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:29,634
Mm. Mm.

484
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:32,992
Good night.

485
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:35,754
Good night.

486
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,668
(Lively chatter)

487
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:54,954
No, Anshel, the point of study is
to teach us how to Live, not only to study.

488
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,156
- Why?
- Again, ''Why?''

489
00:35:57,240 --> 00:36:00,596
My father quoted Hillel, who said... May I?

490
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:03,956
- Hillel said, ''May I?''
- No, may I quote Hillel?

491
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:05,393
Quote, quote.

492
00:36:05,480 --> 00:36:10,634
''He that increases wisdom increases Life. ''
Wisdom is the most important thing.

493
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:12,676
Only as the means to an end.

494
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:15,797
Wisdom is the means.
Living is the end.

495
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:18,633
Then, may I ask you another question?

496
00:36:18,720 --> 00:36:20,597
Ask, ask.

497
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:25,470
If he that increases study increases
wisdom, and therefore Life, then...

498
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:27,278
You can't just grab it...

499
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,715
That's not it. You can do it, so Long as...

500
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:33,634
(Man) That's why the rabbi says
