* I'm not sure I understand

751
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:51,272
* But I Like the way I feel

752
00:52:02,840 --> 00:52:08,073
* La la, la la

753
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:28,198
* Oh, why is it that
every time I close my eyes he's there?

754
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:32,239
* The water shining on his skin,
the sunlight in his hair

755
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:34,788
* And all the while I'm thinking things

756
00:52:34,880 --> 00:52:48,032
* That I can never share with him

757
00:52:48,120 --> 00:52:52,432
* I'm a bundle of confusion

758
00:52:53,480 --> 00:52:57,951
* Yet it has a strange appeal

759
00:52:58,720 --> 00:53:03,953
* Did it all begin with him

760
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:14,393
* And the way he makes me feel?

761
00:53:20,920 --> 00:53:24,276
* I Like the way

762
00:53:24,360 --> 00:53:41,711
* He makes me feel *

763
00:53:45,160 --> 00:53:46,912
(Sighs)

764
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:08,229
(Man) Which is the greater crime,
stealing by day or by night?

765
00:54:08,320 --> 00:54:10,595
- (2nd man) By day.
- By night.

766
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:21,400
- What's wrong?
- That's what I wanna know.

767
00:54:21,480 --> 00:54:25,837
Every morning, you exhaust
the five books of Moses

768
00:54:25,920 --> 00:54:29,469
and the entire mystery of
the universe. This morning, nothing.

769
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:31,915
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

770
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:37,518
Just Like my brother. In a world of your
own, not speaking your mind, moody.

771
00:54:37,600 --> 00:54:39,750
- Who's moody?
- Worried about something?

772
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:41,432
- No.
- Studies?

773
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:44,034
I'm your study partner. Tell me if you are.

774
00:54:44,120 --> 00:54:48,750
With me sitting next to you, why worry?
I know. I'll take you to the matchmaker.

775
00:54:48,840 --> 00:54:52,628
- I'm not going to any matchmaker.
- She’ll give you something nice.

776
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:54,676
Excuse me, gentlemen.

777
00:54:55,800 --> 00:54:57,552
Thank you, Sophie.

778
00:54:57,640 --> 00:54:59,596
Avigdor, please.

779
00:55:01,360 --> 00:55:03,316
My future father-in-Law wants to see me.

780
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,595
- We're going tonight.
- No, now.

781
00:55:05,680 --> 00:55:08,752
- What for?
- Dowry, wedding ceremony...

782
00:55:08,840 --> 00:55:11,877
- the wedding night!
- Why do you keep grabbing me?

783
00:55:11,960 --> 00:55:13,951
What?

784
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:16,190
You're always grabbing me.

785
00:55:17,320 --> 00:55:19,629
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

786
00:55:20,600 --> 00:55:22,955
So? Everything has to have a reason?

787
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:28,796
The wedding night!

788
00:55:36,680 --> 00:55:39,877
(Bell ringing)

789
00:55:57,120 --> 00:55:59,475
Hello, Sophie. Is Avigdor here?

790
00:55:59,560 --> 00:56:03,075
Erm, he, er...

791
00:56:03,160 --> 00:56:04,878
Excuse me.

792
00:56:04,960 --> 00:56:07,315
(Muffled sobbing)

793
00:56:18,240 --> 00:56:20,276
What's... what's wrong?

794
00:56:21,040 --> 00:56:23,429
- (Sobbing)
- What's the matter?

795
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:27,672
Anshel, I'm sorry. You're still welcome,
no matter what's happened.

796
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:30,035
Sophie will get you something to eat.

797
00:56:30,120 --> 00:56:32,395
- (Sobbing)
- Where's Avigdor?

798
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:35,276
Excuse me, Reb Alter, but...

799
00:56:36,480 --> 00:56:39,278
(Esther) Hadass, sweetheart,
try to understand.

800
00:56:45,720 --> 00:56:47,358
Avigdor.

801
00:56:48,080 --> 00:56:49,877
I just came from...

802
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:53,112
What happened?

803
00:56:53,200 --> 00:56:55,395
The wedding's off.

804
00:56:56,520 --> 00:56:58,715
Why?

805
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:02,509
He says I have the evil eye,
says melancholy runs in our blood.

806
00:57:02,600 --> 00:57:03,953
What are you saying?

807
00:57:04,040 --> 00:57:07,919
No man can Let his daughter
marry into a family Like that.

808
00:57:09,680 --> 00:57:12,353
Avigdor, what are you talking about?

809
00:57:12,440 --> 00:57:14,795
- They found out.
- What?

810
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:17,519
- About my brother.
- What about him?

811
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:20,478
He didn't die of pneumonia
or consumption.

812
00:57:20,560 --> 00:57:22,516
He committed suicide.

813
00:57:23,840 --> 00:57:25,876
Oh, my God.

814
00:57:25,960 --> 00:57:27,712
So no wedding.

815
00:57:27,800 --> 00:57:29,518
No sons.

816
00:57:30,480 --> 00:57:32,436
What's all this for?

817
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:37,274
- Did you talk to Hadass?
- What for?

818
00:57:37,360 --> 00:57:39,669
She loves you, she'll still marry you.

819
00:57:39,760 --> 00:57:43,230
- Not if her parents say no.
- If she thinks her parents are wrong...

820
00:57:43,320 --> 00:57:46,278
She's a woman! She can't think for herself.

821
00:57:46,360 --> 00:57:48,316
That's nonsense!

822
00:57:48,400 --> 00:57:50,356
You want a philosophical argument?

823
00:57:50,440 --> 00:57:54,513
I've lost the one girl
that I've ever loved, that I'll ever Love!

824
00:58:01,840 --> 00:58:03,796
You’ll fall in Love again.

825
00:58:07,480 --> 00:58:08,833
No.

826
00:58:10,040 --> 00:58:13,794
Hadass is a nice girl but don't make her
into more than she is.

827
00:58:13,880 --> 00:58:15,632
I'm not.

828
00:58:16,560 --> 00:58:18,516
She was exactly what I wanted.

829
00:58:30,520 --> 00:58:32,476
Please go.

830
00:58:32,560 --> 00:58:35,313
(Thunder)

831
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:39,512
I'm sorry.

832
00:58:39,600 --> 00:58:41,875
Is this really happening, Anshel?

833
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:46,357
Maybe...

834
00:58:46,960 --> 00:58:49,155
someone else will turn up for you.

835
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:57,792
Maybe not... quite as pretty,

836
00:58:57,880 --> 00:59:00,519
maybe with brown hair.

837
00:59:02,600 --> 00:59:04,716
I wouldn’t notice her if she did.

838
00:59:34,960 --> 00:59:36,951
(Thunder)

839
01:00:17,680 --> 01:00:19,557
(Clock ticking)

840
01:00:30,400 --> 01:00:33,312
(Yentl) Why punish him
for something his brother did?

841
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:34,879
Anshel, please.

842
01:00:34,960 --> 01:00:38,077
Hadass should be proud to be his wife.

843
01:00:38,160 --> 01:00:40,913
- Anshel.
- Love is all that matters.

844
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:43,150
No, there are other things.

845
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:45,310
Don't talk old wives' tales, talk the Law.

846
01:00:45,400 --> 01:00:47,789
I'll talk Life!

847
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:50,948
What matters is a man's children.

848
01:00:51,040 --> 01:00:54,635
It's his children that your Law exists for,
her children!

849
01:00:54,720 --> 01:00:56,676
That's her only dowry.

850
01:00:56,760 --> 01:01:01,709
And my obligation as a father.
I have one daughter. I want the best for her.

851
01:01:03,560 --> 01:01:05,437
Avigdor is the best.

852
01:01:05,520 --> 01:01:07,636
The best scholar, maybe, the best friend.

853
01:01:08,520 --> 01:01:10,795
But not the best choice.

854
01:01:10,880 --> 01:01:14,270
We want someone from a good family,

855
01:01:14,360 --> 01:01:18,399
someone with no secrets to hide.

856
01:01:19,200 --> 01:01:20,952
Someone Like...

857
01:01:27,080 --> 01:01:29,036
Someone else.

858
01:01:36,440 --> 01:01:38,271
Anshel.

859
01:01:39,920 --> 01:01:41,797
A Little more?

860
01:01:54,720 --> 01:01:57,632
In the middle of the night,
he goes to school.

861
01:01:57,720 --> 01:01:59,711
What did you have for dinner?

862
01:01:59,800 --> 01:02:01,756
What did I have for dinner?

863
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:04,677
Very Little.

864
01:02:04,760 --> 01:02:06,990
And Hadass?

865
01:02:07,080 --> 01:02:09,275
She's still in Love. What do you expect?

866
01:02:09,360 --> 01:02:10,952
How did she Look?

867
01:02:12,720 --> 01:02:14,836
Not as bad as you do.

868
01:02:17,840 --> 01:02:21,071
You didn't miss anything.
It was Like a madhouse.

869
01:02:21,160 --> 01:02:23,390
The whole family’s going crazy.

870
01:02:23,480 --> 01:02:25,436
What do you mean?

871
01:02:27,240 --> 01:02:29,708
Well, it's just that... (Clears throat)

872
01:02:29,800 --> 01:02:34,157
I'm sure Reb Alter... I mean, to save face,
they're going to try to marry her off...

873
01:02:34,240 --> 01:02:37,676
After a broken engagement,
they have to. It's usual.

874
01:02:37,760 --> 01:02:41,275
- Did they mention someone?
- No, no.

875
01:02:41,360 --> 01:02:45,273
- But they were looking at me.
- You?

876
01:02:45,360 --> 01:02:49,399
(Laughing) Can you imagine?

877
01:02:49,480 --> 01:02:53,155
Shows you how desperate they are.
(Laughing)

878
01:02:54,600 --> 01:02:57,114
(Laughter continues)

879
01:02:59,280 --> 01:03:02,352
- What's the matter?
- The books.

880
01:03:02,960 --> 01:03:05,633
Avigdor? What's the matter?

881
01:03:05,720 --> 01:03:08,154
That's a sin! What are you doing?

882
01:03:08,240 --> 01:03:11,915
Avigdor, please,
just tell me what's happening.

883
01:03:12,000 --> 01:03:14,594
- The books!
- What?

884
01:03:14,680 --> 01:03:16,910
- What are you doing?
- Where is it?

885
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:19,639
- What are you Looking for?
- Oh, here it is.

886
01:03:19,720 --> 01:03:22,359
- What's the matter?
- Sit down. Sit.

887
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:27,592
I...

888
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:31,593
Anshel, I'm going to make you
the happiest man in the world.

889
01:03:31,680 --> 01:03:34,956
- Yes?
- It is the Law, and it's written.

890
01:03:35,040 --> 01:03:36,758
You Like everything written.

891
01:03:36,840 --> 01:03:39,912
- What's written, Avigdor?
- (Speaks Hebrew)

892
01:03:41,360 --> 01:03:43,316
It's perfect. We are Like brothers.

893
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:47,393
If one dies, it is the other's obligation
to marry his widow.

894
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:49,357
Who's died?

895
01:03:49,440 --> 01:03:51,351
I want you to marry Hadass.

896
01:03:52,680 --> 01:03:54,079
- Oh, no.
- Yes.

897
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:56,469
Never, Avigdor, I couldn’t.

898
01:03:56,560 --> 01:03:58,994
- Why not?
- Why not?

899
01:03:59,080 --> 01:04:01,196
- She Loves you.
- Let me explain.

900
01:04:01,280 --> 01:04:03,236
I'm not your brother.

901
01:04:03,320 --> 01:04:06,232
- In my eyes, you are!
- I don't want to marry her!

902
01:04:06,320 --> 01:04:09,153
- I don't Love her!
- That's good!

903
01:04:09,240 --> 01:04:12,994
- What are you talking about?
- Listen! It's meant to be!

904
01:04:13,080 --> 01:04:14,752
Nothing's meant to be.

905
01:04:14,840 --> 01:04:18,515
The thought of her with another man,
a total stranger, drives me crazy.

906
01:04:18,600 --> 01:04:21,956
You marrying her would be
the nearest thing to me marrying her.

907
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:24,759
They may marry her to someone
she doesn't know!

908
01:04:24,840 --> 01:04:27,593
- She could never Love me.
- She likes you.

909
01:04:27,680 --> 01:04:29,750
I could see her, visit you both.

910
01:04:29,840 --> 01:04:31,796
You're talking Like a madman.

911
01:04:31,880 --> 01:04:35,031
If they take her away,
I'll never see her again.

912
01:04:35,120 --> 01:04:37,111
- She’ll take care of you.
- No.

913
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:39,714
- Wealthy family, beautiful girl...
- No!

914
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:43,713
- Why do you have to be different?
- Please, that's enough.

915
01:04:43,800 --> 01:04:47,429
Oh! What's the matter with you?
Any other man would...

916
01:04:49,280 --> 01:04:52,272
Anshel, time will go by.

917
01:04:53,440 --> 01:04:55,556
Tempers cool, things change.

918
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:59,956
Who knows? Perhaps even her father.

919
01:05:00,920 --> 01:05:03,957
Your marriage could be dissolved.
Hadass and I could...

920
01:05:04,040 --> 01:05:05,996
She means that much to you?

921
01:05:08,240 --> 01:05:10,196
Who better will you find?

922
01:05:11,200 --> 01:05:13,760
Who better will she find?

923
01:05:13,840 --> 01:05:17,833
- Do it, for all of us.
- I can't! It's impossible.

924
01:05:17,920 --> 01:05:19,876
Nothing's impossible.

925
01:05:22,120 --> 01:05:24,076
Just think about it.

926
01:05:24,760 --> 01:05:26,716
I've thought.

927
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:29,553
It's out of the question. The answer is no.

928
01:05:42,320 --> 01:05:44,470
Another question.

929
01:05:44,560 --> 01:05:46,516
Do you feel anything for me?

930
01:05:48,280 --> 01:05:49,633
What?

931
01:05:49,720 --> 01:05:51,472
Do you?

932
01:05:52,960 --> 01:05:54,916
Of course I do.

933
01:05:56,800 --> 01:05:58,870
Then think again.

934
01:06:43,960 --> 01:06:46,554
More noodles? They're your favorite.

935
01:06:47,560 --> 01:06:49,516
How do you know?

936
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:51,750
You told me Last week at dinner.

937
01:06:52,880 --> 01:06:55,792
- I don't remember.
- I do.

938
01:07:00,640 --> 01:07:02,596
It's a little chilly in here.

939
01:07:04,560 --> 01:07:06,710
I thought it was rather warm myself.

940
01:07:06,800 --> 01:07:10,156
It is warm... for this time of year.

941
01:07:10,240 --> 01:07:14,438
* No wonder she suits him

942
01:07:14,520 --> 01:07:18,035
* She never disputes him... *

943
01:07:18,120 --> 01:07:20,076
Last year, it was also warm.

944
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:22,116
* The conversation's not too exciting

945
01:07:22,200 --> 01:07:24,430
* But oh, what a change it must be

946
01:07:24,520 --> 01:07:27,034
* To spend an evening
where there's no conversation

947
01:07:27,120 --> 01:07:29,714
- * Must be a relief after me... *
- I'll get dessert.

948
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:32,712
* And though there's nothing much
to challenge your mind here

949
01:07:32,800 --> 01:07:35,997
* Who cares when the food's so delicious?

950
01:07:36,080 --> 01:07:40,198
* Not to mention these beautiful dishes

951
01:07:40,280 --> 01:07:42,589
* A matched set

952
01:07:42,680 --> 01:07:45,274
* From France yet... *

953
01:07:47,280 --> 01:07:49,032
You Look pensive.

954
01:07:49,120 --> 01:07:51,076
No, I was just thinking.

955
01:07:53,040 --> 01:07:54,996
About me?

956
01:07:57,080 --> 01:07:59,036
As a matter of fact, I was.

957
01:08:00,680 --> 01:08:02,636
Good thoughts, I hope.

958
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:08,278
Something smells good. What is it?

959
01:08:08,360 --> 01:08:11,238
It must be the cinnamon
in the baked apple.

960
01:08:12,120 --> 01:08:14,190
You bake apples too?

961
01:08:14,280 --> 01:08:17,909
* No wonder he loves her

962
01:08:18,840 --> 01:08:22,435
* No wonder to me... *

963
01:08:22,520 --> 01:08:24,476
- A cushion?
- Why not?

964
01:08:24,560 --> 01:08:27,757
* With ribbons and laces

965
01:08:27,840 --> 01:08:31,389
* In all the right places... *

966
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:33,755
- Milk or lemon?
- Yes, please.

967
01:08:33,840 --> 01:08:36,912
* I must admit it's all very pleasant
and this is a comfortable room... *

968
01:08:37,000 --> 01:08:38,558
- Which?
- Which what?

969
01:08:38,640 --> 01:08:40,198
* And if he likes the smell
of lilacs and roses

970
01:08:40,280 --> 01:08:43,033
- * Then maybe he likes her perfume... *
- Lemon or milk?

971
01:08:43,120 --> 01:08:46,032
* And though her silky hair
and milky complexion are nice

972
01:08:46,120 --> 01:08:48,714
- * Still they're not that distracting... *
- Anshel?

973
01:08:48,800 --> 01:08:50,472
- Milky.
- What?

974
01:08:50,560 --> 01:08:51,913
Milk, milk!

975
01:08:52,000 --> 01:08:55,037
* So what accounts
for the way he's been acting? *

976
01:08:55,120 --> 01:08:58,271
- Honey?
- * Her softness... *

977
01:08:58,360 --> 01:09:01,272
- No honey.
- * Her sweetness... *

978
01:09:01,360 --> 01:09:03,351
Sugar?

979
01:09:03,440 --> 01:09:07,752
* How could he resist her? *

980
01:09:07,840 --> 01:09:11,594
- An almond cookie?
- * And why would he try? *

981
01:09:11,680 --> 01:09:13,636
How do you get them all the same size?

982
01:09:13,720 --> 01:09:17,429
* No wonder he wants her... *

983
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:20,114
- You notice everything.
- * He needs her... *

984
01:09:20,200 --> 01:09:22,794
The china. Cookies.

985
01:09:22,880 --> 01:09:26,873
* No wonder... *

986
01:09:26,960 --> 01:09:29,076
That's really wonderful.

987
01:09:30,680 --> 01:09:34,195
* So would I *

988
01:09:34,280 --> 01:09:38,319
Where are your parents?
Maybe they'd Like some tea.

989
01:09:38,400 --> 01:09:42,473
They're in the study
having tea with a guest from Zamosc.

990
01:09:42,560 --> 01:09:45,074
Yesterday, two came from Tomashev.

991
01:09:45,160 --> 01:09:46,639
I must be going.

992
01:09:46,720 --> 01:09:50,599
I may have to leave Bechev
if they don't find someone for me here.

993
01:09:50,680 --> 01:09:54,355
They'll find someone.
Who wouldn’t want you? I mean...

994
01:09:54,440 --> 01:09:57,716
- Don't you think about marriage?
- No, just my studies.

995
01:09:57,800 --> 01:10:00,633
- I admire that in a man.
- That's very good.

996
01:10:01,920 --> 01:10:03,672
Good night.

997
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:06,113
Good night.

998
01:10:19,840 --> 01:10:22,400
He's not there, Anshel.

999
01:10:23,560 --> 01:10:26,757
He's gone. He took his things and Left.

1000
01:10:31,080 --> 01:10:32,638
Hurry!

1001
01:10:32,720 --> 01:10:35,598
Wagons to Lublin province leaving now!

1002
01:10:35,680 --> 01:10:39,150
Wagons to Lublin province
Leaving now!

1003
01:10:39,240 --> 01:10:41,674
Avigdor, don't leave! I was wrong!

1004
01:10:41,760 --> 01:10:44,593
- You?
- She's worth fighting for!

1005
01:10:44,680 --> 01:10:47,274
- Talk to Vishkower.
- He won't listen!

1006
01:10:47,360 --> 01:10:51,148
- Maybe there's a Law.
- There are no laws, not for this.

1007
01:10:51,240 --> 01:10:56,155
If you stopped studying once in a while,
you'd know more about Life, about Love.

1008
01:10:57,840 --> 01:11:00,070
How can I expect you to understand?

1009
01:11:00,160 --> 01:11:02,116
You've never felt it.

1010
01:11:05,680 --> 01:11:08,148
Last call for Lublin province!

1011
01:11:08,240 --> 01:11:10,117
Avigdor!

1012
01:11:11,080 --> 01:11:13,310
(Baby crying)

1013
01:11:13,400 --> 01:11:15,834
- Oh, my God.
- Carry your suitcase, sir?

1014
01:11:21,720 --> 01:11:24,029
Bye, Anshel.

1015
01:11:24,120 --> 01:11:26,509
I'm sorry about everything.

1016
01:11:26,600 --> 01:11:29,717
Asking what I did was
my only way of staying and it was wrong.

1017
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:33,270
No, it's not wrong. It's understandable.
You're in Love.

1018
01:11:33,360 --> 01:11:35,954
- It was sinful, unnatural.
- But what's natural?

1019
01:11:36,040 --> 01:11:39,874
- I was asking the impossible.
- Don't go, Avigdor!

1020
01:11:39,960 --> 01:11:41,996
Everyone aboard!

1021
01:11:42,080 --> 01:11:44,150
Don't go!

1022
01:11:44,240 --> 01:11:46,674
I'll come with you!

1023
01:11:55,080 --> 01:11:57,594
Wait! Avigdor!

1024
01:11:57,680 --> 01:11:59,910
Nothing's impossible!

1025
01:12:03,720 --> 01:12:05,597
Nothing.

1026
01:12:14,360 --> 01:12:15,679
It's impossible.

1027
01:12:15,760 --> 01:12:19,912
What do you think, Zelig?
I never had such trouble fitting anybody.

1028
01:12:20,000 --> 01:12:22,309
- It's so tight round the chest.
- It fits!

1029
01:12:22,400 --> 01:12:24,914
- This is how you cut.
- It's the tape measure.

1030
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:26,513
It's all right.

1031
01:12:26,600 --> 01:12:29,672
For Alter Vishkower's son-in-Law,
we must do our best work.

1032
01:12:29,760 --> 01:12:33,196
- I Like it this way.
- He Likes it this way! Ha!

1033
01:12:35,360 --> 01:12:37,749
- Look at him.
- * Look at me

1034
01:12:39,080 --> 01:12:42,311
* I must be absolutely crazy

1035
01:12:42,400 --> 01:12:44,436
* How did I ever let it get this far? *

1036
01:12:44,520 --> 01:12:46,158
Take off the coat.

1037
01:12:46,240 --> 01:12:48,754
* I’m getting deeper into trouble

1038
01:12:48,840 --> 01:12:51,593
* Am I a woman or a man?
Am I a devil or a demon?

1039
01:12:51,680 --> 01:12:55,878
Problem with the pants. Next to them,
the coat looks good. Take them off.

1040
01:12:55,960 --> 01:12:57,313
- Why?
- Why?

1041
01:12:57,400 --> 01:12:59,436
* Papa was right

1042
01:12:59,520 --> 01:13:02,751
* I ask too many questions
he said a soul can get perplexed

1043
01:13:02,840 --> 01:13:05,354
* I can't believe what happens next
Papa was right! *

1044
01:13:05,440 --> 01:13:07,510
- Trouble with the crotch.
- What's wrong?

1045
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:09,909
You’ll find out when you relieve yourself.

1046
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:13,037
* It seems this little game I play
becomes more risky every day *

1047
01:13:13,120 --> 01:13:15,873
- The pants, please.
- All right, I'll take them off.

1048
01:13:15,960 --> 01:13:18,918
- Leave the room.
- He's ashamed.

1049
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:22,117
A tailor is Like a doctor.
What's to be ashamed?

1050
01:13:22,200 --> 01:13:25,670
Move, Zelig!
The wedding's tomorrow night!

1051
01:13:28,320 --> 01:13:29,878
(Tailor) Move!

1052
01:13:29,960 --> 01:13:33,316
Tomorrow night? Tomorrow night?

1053
01:13:35,040 --> 01:13:39,955
* Tomorrow night, tomorrow night

1054
01:13:40,040 --> 01:13:45,478
* Under the canopy I'll stand with her
tomorrow night

1055
01:13:45,560 --> 01:13:47,869
* And place a ring upon her hand

1056
01:13:47,960 --> 01:13:51,475
* With her all dressed in white

1057
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:53,312
* Tomorrow night

1058
01:13:53,400 --> 01:13:56,039
* I don't know how this came about
but I'll be wed without a doubt

1059
01:13:56,120 --> 01:13:59,237
- * I've got to get out! *
- (Tailor) What did you say?

1060
01:13:59,320 --> 01:14:01,595
I've got to get out of my clothes.

1061
01:14:01,680 --> 01:14:04,274
Get back out here.

1062
01:14:05,320 --> 01:14:08,312
- * Look at this... *
- Come on, move.

1063
01:14:08,400 --> 01:14:11,517
* The way one lie begets another

1064
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:13,955
* Somebody wake me up
and say it's all a dream... *

1065
01:14:14,040 --> 01:14:16,474
- Ouch!
- Look at this!

1066
01:14:16,560 --> 01:14:18,835
* Look how easily I fool them

1067
01:14:18,920 --> 01:14:21,718
* They may have eyes but they don't see
they never really look at me

1068
01:14:21,800 --> 01:14:23,518
* People are blind

1069
01:14:23,600 --> 01:14:26,512
* How else would everyone believe me?

1070
01:14:26,600 --> 01:14:29,637
* It might be interesting to know
just how much further I can go... *

1071
01:14:29,720 --> 01:14:32,473
Look, the right sieve
is Longer than the Left!

1072
01:14:32,560 --> 01:14:34,949
- This will never work.
- We’ll make it work!

1073
01:14:35,880 --> 01:14:37,677
At Least the hat fits.

1074
01:14:37,760 --> 01:14:42,390
* Tomorrow night, tomorrow night

1075
01:14:42,480 --> 01:14:45,472
* I can't believe what I'll presume to be

1076
01:14:45,560 --> 01:14:48,154
* Tomorrow night

1077
01:14:48,240 --> 01:14:51,232
* I’m not the bride,
but I’m the groom-to-be

1078
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:53,788
* Tomorrow night

1079
01:14:53,880 --> 01:14:56,519
* And that's a monumental trick
I'd better think of something quick *

1080
01:14:56,600 --> 01:14:58,556
Oh, my God, I'm feeling sick!

1081
01:14:58,640 --> 01:15:01,473
Just the usual nerves before the wedding.

1082
01:15:01,560 --> 01:15:05,439
- I'd better rest.
- You’ll need plenty of rest!

1083
01:15:05,520 --> 01:15:08,193
* I could run away

1084
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:10,316
* I could leave without a trace

1085
01:15:10,400 --> 01:15:12,675
* Go anywhere or anyplace

1086
01:15:12,760 --> 01:15:17,072
* Where no one knows my face
as a woman or a man

1087
01:15:17,160 --> 01:15:21,756
* I don't know, just so I can run away

1088
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:24,593
* Run away

1089
01:15:24,680 --> 01:15:26,113
* I’d be free

1090
01:15:26,200 --> 01:15:28,998
* I’d be rid of all of this

1091
01:15:29,080 --> 01:15:33,312
* But there's someone I would miss

1092
01:15:34,720 --> 01:15:38,315
* And being near him is what this

1093
01:15:38,400 --> 01:15:40,994
* Is all about

1094
01:15:41,800 --> 01:15:45,475
* So running away is out

1095
01:15:45,560 --> 01:15:48,950
(Zelig) Will he get away with it?
(Tailor) Will we get away with it?

1096
01:15:49,040 --> 01:15:50,712
* Papa, dear

1097
01:15:50,800 --> 01:15:53,872
* You dreamed of dancing at my wedding

1098
01:15:55,400 --> 01:15:59,712
* But something tells me that I’m right
you wouldn't want to dance tonight *

1099
01:16:03,800 --> 01:16:06,758
Take off the clothes.
All right. We’ll Leave the room.

1100
01:16:06,840 --> 01:16:10,071
Come, Zelig, we have a Lot of work to do.

1101
01:16:11,080 --> 01:16:13,071
* Isn't this

1102
01:16:13,160 --> 01:16:15,435
* A strangely logical solution?

1103
01:16:16,360 --> 01:16:20,319
* Things may not be as they appear
but the advantages are clear

1104
01:16:22,360 --> 01:16:23,873
* He loves her, she loves him

1105
01:16:23,960 --> 01:16:25,473
* He Likes me, I Like her

1106
01:16:25,560 --> 01:16:28,233
* And I've reason to think she Likes me

1107
01:16:28,320 --> 01:16:31,118
* She keeps him, he keeps her
I keep things as they were

1108
01:16:31,200 --> 01:16:33,794
* It's a perfect arrangement for three

1109
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:36,235
* Who'd have ever predicted
the moment would come

1110
01:16:36,320 --> 01:16:38,993
* When I’d find myself grateful
they've kept women dumb?

1111
01:16:39,080 --> 01:16:41,753
* She's an innocent maiden,
but then, so am I

1112
01:16:41,840 --> 01:16:43,990
* That's why it's possible
I could get by

1113
01:16:44,080 --> 01:16:46,833
* Look, I’ve seen the impossible
happen before

1114
01:16:46,920 --> 01:16:49,309
* Maybe, God willing,
it’ll happen once more

1115
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:51,868
* For I feel like a train on a perilous track

1116
01:16:51,960 --> 01:16:53,598
* No way to stop, no way to go back

1117
01:16:53,680 --> 01:16:55,557
* A snowball that's gathering speed
down a hill

1118
01:16:55,640 --> 01:16:59,189
* Going faster and faster and faster until

1119
01:16:59,280 --> 01:17:04,400
* Tomorrow night, tomorrow night

1120
01:17:04,480 --> 01:17:07,472
* Even if someone would pray for me

1121
01:17:07,560 --> 01:17:09,710
* Tomorrow night

1122
01:17:10,320 --> 01:17:13,232
* There's not a prayer
that they could say for me

1123
01:17:13,320 --> 01:17:15,470
* Tomorrow night

1124
01:17:16,320 --> 01:17:19,995
* Tomorrow night, tomorrow night,
tomorrow night

1125
01:17:20,080 --> 01:17:27,589
* Is now tonight! *

1126
01:17:27,680 --> 01:17:29,238
(All cheering)

1127
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:31,959
(All) Mazel tov!
(Man) Blessings!

1128
01:17:32,040 --> 01:17:34,918
Success! Mazel tov!

1129
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:36,877
(Drowned out by chatter)

1130
01:17:38,200 --> 01:17:40,475
(Rabbi) Musicians, please!

1131
01:17:40,560 --> 01:17:43,552
The mitzvah dance!
The handkerchief dance!

1132
01:17:49,480 --> 01:17:52,677
- Excuse me.
- (Rabbi) Where are you going?

1133
01:17:52,760 --> 01:17:55,228
(Tailor) Look. Look at the shoulders.

1134
01:17:58,200 --> 01:18:00,156
You're not Leaving, are you?

1135
01:18:00,240 --> 01:18:02,834
I have a wedding present for both of you.

1136
01:18:02,920 --> 01:18:05,514
- Thank you.
- Nachmonides, the holy letter.

1137
01:18:05,600 --> 01:18:08,114
He wrote it over 500 years ago.

1138
01:18:08,200 --> 01:18:10,998
''Converse with her
to put her mind at ease.

1139
01:18:11,080 --> 01:18:16,677
''Speak words which arouse her to Love,
desire, and passion,

1140
01:18:16,760 --> 01:18:19,399
''and words of reverence for God. ''

1141
01:18:21,800 --> 01:18:23,756
Never force her.

1142
01:18:23,840 --> 01:18:26,149
Her mood must be as yours.

1143
01:18:26,920 --> 01:18:30,390
Win her with graciousness
and seductiveness.

1144
01:18:31,560 --> 01:18:35,314
Be patient until her passion is aroused.

1145
01:18:36,880 --> 01:18:38,711
Begin with Love.

1146
01:18:38,800 --> 01:18:40,916
And when her mood is ready,

1147
01:18:41,800 --> 01:18:44,439
Let her desire be satisfied first.

1148
01:18:45,440 --> 01:18:47,874
Her delight is what matters.

1149
01:18:47,960 --> 01:18:50,758
(Women talking appreciatively)

1150
01:18:50,840 --> 01:18:53,638
- (* Lively music)
- Come along.

1151
01:18:55,720 --> 01:18:59,759
- Avigdor, I... I don't know if I can...
- (Alter) Anshel.

1152
01:18:59,840 --> 01:19:02,479
- Anshel.
- Your father-in-law's calling you.

1153
01:19:02,560 --> 01:19:05,154
(* Lively music continues)

1154
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:07,629
Anshel, I have to talk to you.

1155
01:19:07,720 --> 01:19:11,508
Remember your obligation.
As I said, you mustn't be nervous.

1156
01:19:13,680 --> 01:19:18,470
Eve was made from Adam's rib
to obey his wishes. So must you.

1157
01:19:18,560 --> 01:19:21,791
- There's nothing to be nervous about.
- Yes, Mother.

1158
01:19:21,880 --> 01:19:24,440
We have protected her. She knows nothing.

1159
01:19:24,520 --> 01:19:27,796
But I don't have to tell you
to be fruitful and multiply.

1160
01:19:27,880 --> 01:19:29,836
Thank you, sir, I know the Law.

1161
01:19:29,920 --> 01:19:33,674
May your wedding night
be as joyful as ours... was.

1162
01:19:34,800 --> 01:19:38,270
And, please God,
a grandson nine months from now.

1163
01:19:42,720 --> 01:19:44,915
(* Lively music)

1164
01:19:52,160 --> 01:19:54,913
(Music and laughter downstairs)

1165
01:20:45,920 --> 01:20:47,672
Are you too warm?

1166
01:20:48,400 --> 01:20:50,118
(Hadass) No.

1167
01:20:50,960 --> 01:20:53,155
- Shall I open a window?
- No.

1168
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:56,710
Unless you want to. You're the man.

1169
01:20:58,080 --> 01:20:59,832
That's true.

1170
01:21:02,400 --> 01:21:04,550
- Don't be frightened.
- I'm not.

1171
01:21:04,640 --> 01:21:06,437
You're not?

1172
01:21:06,520 --> 01:21:09,034
- Yes, I am.
- Good.

1173
01:21:09,120 --> 01:21:12,112
- What?
- I mean, it's only natural.

1174
01:21:13,600 --> 01:21:17,149
You don't have to do
anything you don't want to. Anything.

1175
01:21:17,240 --> 01:21:20,232
But I do. I have to do
whatever you demand.

1176
01:21:20,320 --> 01:21:23,073
- No, that's not so.
- It's not?

1177
01:21:23,160 --> 01:21:26,835
The Talmud says a woman
may refuse her husband.

1178
01:21:26,920 --> 01:21:29,878
- My mother said...
- Too many women don't know the Law!

1179
01:21:29,960 --> 01:21:33,157
If you want to refuse
then naturally I respect your wishes.

1180
01:21:34,720 --> 01:21:37,314
You're a very considerate man, Anshel.

1181
01:21:38,200 --> 01:21:41,510
Only because I know
you're thinking of someone else.

1182
01:21:41,600 --> 01:21:44,194
Who? I'm not at all, of anyone.

1183
01:21:44,280 --> 01:21:46,236
You mustn't be angry with him.

1184
01:21:46,320 --> 01:21:47,799
What?

1185
01:21:47,880 --> 01:21:51,475
Well, any woman would be
who was close to him.

1186
01:21:53,480 --> 01:21:55,471
You're very understanding.

1187
01:21:56,720 --> 01:21:59,996
It's only natural that you wish he were here
instead of me.

1188
01:22:00,080 --> 01:22:01,752
But you're my husband.

1189
01:22:01,840 --> 01:22:06,311
The thing is, Hadass,
because you're still thinking of Avigdor,

1190
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:10,154
I can't Let you commit any unnecessary sin.

1191
01:22:10,240 --> 01:22:11,992
- Sin?
- It's clearly written

1192
01:22:12,080 --> 01:22:16,676
that a woman cannot give herself to one
man while she's thinking of another.

1193
01:22:16,760 --> 01:22:20,673
Tonight we'll do what you want,
which is nothing, I understand.

1194
01:22:20,760 --> 01:22:23,832
- I don't know what I want.
- When you do,

1195
01:22:23,920 --> 01:22:26,070
you must Let me know.

1196
01:22:27,560 --> 01:22:30,472
You're very hard to resist, Hadass,

1197
01:22:30,560 --> 01:22:33,836
but I'm not going to force myself on you.

1198
01:22:33,920 --> 01:22:37,390
I'll... I'll just have to be patient.

1199
01:22:39,680 --> 01:22:42,319
- Good.
- Good.

1200
01:22:46,920 --> 01:22:49,275
Ah! A drop more wine?

1201
01:22:49,360 --> 01:22:51,555
(Yentl chuckles)

1202
01:22:51,640 --> 01:22:54,518
It's our secret. No one needs to know.

1203
01:22:54,600 --> 01:22:56,318
Our secret.

1204
01:22:57,920 --> 01:22:59,876
And our friendship.

1205
01:22:59,960 --> 01:23:03,191
- A husband and wife can be friends?
- Oh, yes.

1206
01:23:03,280 --> 01:23:07,068
There's only one problem. Help me.

1207
01:23:07,160 --> 01:23:10,118
In the morning, when they come in,
they'll think we've...

1208
01:23:10,200 --> 01:23:12,395
- But we haven't!
- Shh! Secret!

1209
01:23:12,480 --> 01:23:14,550
- Shh!
- (Both giggling)

1210
01:23:18,800 --> 01:23:20,950
Wait, no, just one bed.

1211
01:23:21,960 --> 01:23:24,713
(Giggling)

1212
01:23:27,480 --> 01:23:29,596
- You silly goose!
- (Laughter)

1213
01:23:34,200 --> 01:23:36,668
(Laughter continues)

1214
01:23:43,520 --> 01:23:46,239
- (Crash)
- Ooh!

1215
01:23:47,720 --> 01:23:49,676
You tell me.

1216
01:23:52,240 --> 01:23:54,196
Truce, truce!

1217
01:23:54,280 --> 01:23:56,236
(Both Laughing)

1218
01:23:56,320 --> 01:23:58,515
(Hadass) Oh!

1219
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:09,596
(Hadass sighs)

1220
01:24:10,960 --> 01:24:12,518
Anshel.

1221
01:24:15,480 --> 01:24:18,677
I think I'm going to Like
being married to you.

1222
01:24:23,880 --> 01:24:26,155
Good night, Hadass.

1223
01:24:26,240 --> 01:24:28,196
Good night.

1224
01:24:30,360 --> 01:24:31,759
(Burp)

1225
01:24:31,840 --> 01:24:33,796
(Laughter)

1226
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:39,592
(Avigdor) So, er... what was it Like?

1227
01:24:39,680 --> 01:24:42,638
- Oh, the usual. Music, dancing...
- I was there.

1228
01:24:42,720 --> 01:24:44,472
Oh.

1229
01:24:44,560 --> 01:24:47,199
Hadass and I talked, laughed a little...

1230
01:24:47,280 --> 01:24:48,838
Laughed a Lot.

1231
01:24:48,920 --> 01:24:50,797
And then she went to sleep.

1232
01:24:50,880 --> 01:24:52,836
Tell me the truth.

1233
01:24:52,920 --> 01:24:55,070
People who want the truth never believe it.

1234
01:24:55,160 --> 01:24:58,232
- What did you do to her?
- What do you think I did to her?

1235
01:24:58,320 --> 01:25:00,914
You kissed her, caressed her, held her.

1236
01:25:01,000 --> 01:25:05,710
All right! I did everything Like you said.
What else do you want to know?

1237
01:25:05,800 --> 01:25:07,756
Did she make sounds? Did she scream... ?

1238
01:25:07,840 --> 01:25:11,674
- She screamed and went to sleep.
- Went to sleep?

1239
01:25:11,760 --> 01:25:13,910
- Anshel.
- She talked a Little.

1240
01:25:14,000 --> 01:25:17,037
Talked? In her sleep? What did she say?

1241
01:25:17,120 --> 01:25:19,156
Things Like, ''Avigdor, I Love you. ''

1242
01:25:19,240 --> 01:25:21,196
''I Love you''?

1243
01:25:22,600 --> 01:25:24,113
Go on.

1244
01:25:26,720 --> 01:25:30,349
''I adore you, Avigdor, '' she said.

1245
01:25:33,120 --> 01:25:34,633
That's the truth?

1246
01:25:35,920 --> 01:25:37,717
Yes, my friend.

1247
01:25:38,760 --> 01:25:40,716
That's the truth.

1248
01:26:00,640 --> 01:26:03,598
Raspberry tea
is very good for headaches.

1249
01:26:06,280 --> 01:26:09,909
- Thank you.
- Am I disturbing you?

1250
01:26:10,000 --> 01:26:11,558
No.

1251
01:26:15,760 --> 01:26:18,149
It's almost sundown, the Sabbath.

1252
01:26:19,320 --> 01:26:21,117
Yes.

1253
01:26:22,040 --> 01:26:26,318
Mother says it's a special blessing
on the Sabbath.

1254
01:26:26,400 --> 01:26:29,437
- Going to synagogue?
- Going to bed.

1255
01:26:30,920 --> 01:26:32,399
Mm.

1256
01:26:32,480 --> 01:26:34,948
- Unless you're tired.
- What?

1257
01:26:37,440 --> 01:26:40,034
Drink your tea. It's getting cold.

1258
01:26:46,320 --> 01:26:49,278
When Avigdor used to call,
I sometimes spilled things.

1259
01:26:49,360 --> 01:26:52,318
- I don't know if you ever noticed.
- No, never.

1260
01:26:52,400 --> 01:26:56,632
It's because he made me tremble, inside.

1261
01:26:58,400 --> 01:27:00,470
That's Love, Hadass.

1262
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:02,710
But you don't make me tremble.

1263
01:27:05,960 --> 01:27:07,916
You make me peaceful.

1264
01:27:10,520 --> 01:27:13,910
That's the friendship
I was telling you about.

1265
01:27:14,000 --> 01:27:16,912
- In the Talmud...
- So will you teach me?

1266
01:27:18,760 --> 01:27:20,716
Teach you?

1267
01:27:22,040 --> 01:27:23,393
Please?

1268
01:27:25,120 --> 01:27:27,873
- Talmud?
- Talmud?

1269
01:27:27,960 --> 01:27:30,520
- Talmud!
- Not the Talmud.

1270
01:27:30,600 --> 01:27:35,754
Talmud! It's the Least a husband can do
for his wife, the most maybe.

1271
01:27:35,840 --> 01:27:37,796
I could never Learn Talmud.

1272
01:27:37,880 --> 01:27:39,996
Nonsense! Lock the door.

1273
01:27:40,080 --> 01:27:43,038
- Isn't it a sin?
- It's not a sin.

1274
01:27:43,120 --> 01:27:46,476
Then why are we closing the curtains
and locking the door?

1275
01:27:46,560 --> 01:27:50,473
God will understand.
I'm not so sure about the neighbors.

1276
01:27:50,560 --> 01:27:52,516
- (Laughs)
- What's funny?

1277
01:27:52,600 --> 01:27:54,716
You. I've never seen you so excited.

1278
01:27:54,800 --> 01:27:58,270
Now pay attention, Hadass.
First there's the Bible,

1279
01:27:58,360 --> 01:28:00,999
- the five books of Moses...
- Wait.

1280
01:28:01,080 --> 01:28:04,311
- Where are you going?
- The soup's on the stove...

1281
01:28:04,400 --> 01:28:07,198
Let your mother do it, please!

1282
01:28:07,280 --> 01:28:10,511
The Talmud is commentaries
interpreting the...

1283
01:28:10,600 --> 01:28:13,478
- What are you doing?
- Just pulling a thread...

1284
01:28:13,560 --> 01:28:15,755
- Don't! We're studying!
- Yes, Anshel.

1285
01:28:15,840 --> 01:28:18,832
- Where was I?
- Commentaries interpreting the Bible.

1286
01:28:19,920 --> 01:28:21,797
Yes.

1287
01:28:21,880 --> 01:28:25,236
The first commentary is the Mishna,
our code of Law.

1288
01:28:25,320 --> 01:28:27,550
I'm glad your headache's better.

1289
01:28:29,320 --> 01:28:33,711
It's a masterpiece of literature, folklore,
and philosophy,

1290
01:28:33,800 --> 01:28:36,268
it deals with astronomy,
architecture, medicine.

1291
01:28:36,360 --> 01:28:39,318
Everything from making Love
to planting Egyptian beans.

1292
01:28:39,400 --> 01:28:41,868
Making Love?

1293
01:28:41,960 --> 01:28:44,155
To planting Egyptian beans.

1294
01:28:44,240 --> 01:28:46,913
I thought you said something about
making Love.

1295
01:28:47,000 --> 01:28:51,710
Then there's the midrash -
legends, stories, dealing with legal issues.

1296
01:28:51,800 --> 01:28:55,679
Two men dispute
the ownership of a flock of chickens...

1297
01:28:55,760 --> 01:28:58,194
While your books argue about chickens,

1298
01:28:58,280 --> 01:29:00,555
I've had to pluck them.

1299
01:29:00,640 --> 01:29:03,393
It's Friday. I've been up since dawn.

1300
01:29:03,480 --> 01:29:08,349
I'm too tired to be
a scholar on Fridays, Anshel.

1301
01:29:08,440 --> 01:29:10,396
I'm sorry.

1302
01:29:11,640 --> 01:29:13,756
I'm the one who's sorry, Hadass.

1303
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:18,913
I'm too tired
for the special Sabbath blessing,

1304
01:29:19,000 --> 01:29:23,994
even if maybe you were
going to... demand it...

1305
01:29:24,080 --> 01:29:25,433
Maybe.

1306
01:29:27,600 --> 01:29:29,795
(Quiet snoring)

1307
01:29:29,880 --> 01:29:31,916
(Bell tolling)

1308
01:29:37,280 --> 01:29:39,032
(Lively chatter)

1309
01:29:41,840 --> 01:29:43,990
Next Tuesday, eight o’clock.

1310
01:29:45,560 --> 01:29:47,516
What about her parents?

1311
01:29:47,600 --> 01:29:50,433
I'll just say, ''Avigdor's coming to dinner. ''

1312
01:29:50,520 --> 01:29:52,556
Anyway, they're away next Tuesday.

1313
01:29:52,640 --> 01:29:54,995
Are you two agreeing or disagreeing?

1314
01:29:55,080 --> 01:29:56,513
- Agreeing.
- Disagreeing.

1315
01:29:56,600 --> 01:29:57,999
- Disagreeing.
- Agreeing.

1316
01:30:00,360 --> 01:30:03,352
- (Hadass) He's one second late.
- Hm?

1317
01:30:04,440 --> 01:30:06,556
Oh... yes.

1318
01:30:07,200 --> 01:30:09,156
(Doorbell)

1319
01:30:12,040 --> 01:30:14,554
- Hello, Sophie.
- I'll take your hat.

1320
01:30:20,480 --> 01:30:22,311
(Yentl) Thank you, Sophie.

1321
01:30:23,480 --> 01:30:25,232
Hello.

1322
01:30:31,800 --> 01:30:34,712
This is the one I brought from home.

1323
01:30:36,040 --> 01:30:38,395
The first part's about the ancient mystics.

1324
01:30:38,480 --> 01:30:40,675
It's all a bit elementary, but...

1325
01:30:45,400 --> 01:30:47,277
Welcome, Avigdor.

1326
01:30:47,360 --> 01:30:49,430
(Yentl and Hadass Laughing)

1327
01:30:49,520 --> 01:30:52,432
- (Hadass) Tell me more.
- I've told you everything.

1328
01:30:52,520 --> 01:30:55,193
(Hadass) It was a very interesting
discussion.

1329
01:30:55,280 --> 01:30:57,396
And then what happened?

1330
01:30:58,400 --> 01:31:01,472
Well, erm... Avigdor was there too.
He'll tell you.

1331
01:31:02,600 --> 01:31:05,194
Was Rabbi Zalman angry or did he laugh?

1332
01:31:05,280 --> 01:31:08,238
He... he laughed. Didn't he, Avigdor?

1333
01:31:08,320 --> 01:31:10,436
- Yes.
- Did you laugh?

1334
01:31:12,320 --> 01:31:14,197
We both did.

1335
01:31:14,280 --> 01:31:16,236
I can just see you.

1336
01:31:25,040 --> 01:31:27,793
- I'll do that.
- No.

1337
01:31:27,880 --> 01:31:29,836
But you have a guest.

1338
01:31:29,920 --> 01:31:31,876
So have you.

1339
01:31:41,560 --> 01:31:44,279
(Avigdor) Marriage agrees with you.

1340
01:31:44,360 --> 01:31:47,750
- You're more beautiful than ever.
- Thank you.

1341
01:31:47,840 --> 01:31:50,877
Avigdor, I'm concerned about Anshel.

1342
01:31:52,040 --> 01:31:55,635
- What are you talking about?
- I don't think Anshel is happy.

1343
01:31:59,880 --> 01:32:02,348
Why don't we have tea in the parlor?

1344
01:32:06,000 --> 01:32:08,753
Milk or, er... Lemon?

1345
01:32:10,000 --> 01:32:11,399
Fine.

1346
01:32:12,520 --> 01:32:14,476
(Hadass) Ah!

1347
01:32:18,520 --> 01:32:20,272
Sorry.

1348
01:32:21,160 --> 01:32:24,118
(* Hadass humming melody)

1349
01:32:26,760 --> 01:32:30,594
We Left off with Maimonides' code
of the golden rule.

1350
01:32:30,680 --> 01:32:33,240
(Humming)

1351
01:32:35,560 --> 01:32:40,270
Let's read chapters seven and eight
and then discuss them. Is that all right?

1352
01:32:40,360 --> 01:32:42,635
- All right.
- (Stops humming)

1353
01:32:43,720 --> 01:32:46,234
Don't stop, Hadass. It's pretty.

1354
01:32:48,160 --> 01:32:51,357
(Humming)

1355
01:33:00,600 --> 01:33:02,989
* Look at how he looks at her

1356
01:33:03,080 --> 01:33:11,397
* Will someone ever look at me that way?

1357
01:33:12,360 --> 01:33:14,430
* Full of all the feelings

1358
01:33:14,520 --> 01:33:22,916
* And the soft unspoken words
that lovers say

1359
01:33:23,440 --> 01:33:26,716
* I thought that I knew every single look

1360
01:33:26,800 --> 01:33:30,349
* And sweet expression on his face

1361
01:33:30,440 --> 01:33:34,956
* Yet this is one that I don't recognize

1362
01:33:35,040 --> 01:33:40,592
* Although I’ve sat
and studied him for hours

1363
01:33:40,680 --> 01:33:46,710
* But now I see how love
completely occupies

1364
01:33:46,800 --> 01:33:49,633
* A pair of eyes

1365
01:33:50,400 --> 01:33:52,868
* See the way they gaze at her

1366
01:33:52,960 --> 01:34:01,789
* Like slaves they follow
everywhere she goes

1367
01:34:01,880 --> 01:34:04,314
* Do my eyes forget themselves

1368
01:34:04,400 --> 01:34:07,198
* And do I ever look at him

1369
01:34:07,280 --> 01:34:09,475
* And smile in such a way

1370
01:34:09,560 --> 01:34:13,235
* That what I’m feeling shows?

1371
01:34:13,320 --> 01:34:15,959
* Sometimes I have the feeling

1372
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:19,476
* Everybody knows

1373
01:34:19,560 --> 01:34:22,313
* And even though it's crazy

1374
01:34:22,400 --> 01:34:29,909
* Still I can't help wondering
if I'll ever live to see that day

1375
01:34:30,000 --> 01:34:33,675
* When by some

1376
01:34:34,280 --> 01:34:37,078
* Miracle of miracles

1377
01:34:37,160 --> 01:34:43,793
* He'll turn around and look at me

1378
01:34:45,080 --> 01:34:49,153
* That way... *

1379
01:34:49,240 --> 01:34:53,233
It's no good. I'm sorry. Excuse me.

1380
01:34:53,320 --> 01:34:54,912
Avigdor.

1381
01:34:55,000 --> 01:34:56,592
Avigdor, wait!

1382
01:34:56,680 --> 01:34:58,432
(Avigdor) Good night.

1383
01:35:07,960 --> 01:35:09,473
Anshel.

1384
01:35:09,560 --> 01:35:11,118
(Yentl) Hm?

1385
01:35:11,680 --> 01:35:13,636
How many children do you want?

1386
01:35:16,840 --> 01:35:21,789
The actual number?
I don't think I've ever really...

1387
01:35:21,880 --> 01:35:24,633
He didn't make me tremble tonight.

1388
01:35:24,720 --> 01:35:26,711
(Yentl) Hm?

1389
01:35:26,800 --> 01:35:28,552
You did, though.

1390
01:35:30,400 --> 01:35:33,631
What's even nicer, I made you tremble.

1391
01:35:33,720 --> 01:35:35,278
What?

1392
01:35:35,360 --> 01:35:38,670
When he was Leaving,
I put my hand on yours.

1393
01:35:38,760 --> 01:35:40,512
You were trembling.

1394
01:35:40,600 --> 01:35:44,036
Er, well... What are you doing, Hadass?

1395
01:35:44,120 --> 01:35:47,396
- I'm Looking at you.
- I can't read without my glasses.

1396
01:35:47,480 --> 01:35:50,358
When you told me I could refuse you,

1397
01:35:50,440 --> 01:35:53,796
you didn't tell me I also could demand you.

1398
01:35:53,880 --> 01:35:55,836
Who told you that?

1399
01:35:55,920 --> 01:35:59,629
The Talmud. I forget what page.

1400
01:35:59,720 --> 01:36:02,359
- 63a and b.
- It's written, Anshel.

1401
01:36:02,440 --> 01:36:05,034
You've been studying too hard.

1402
01:36:05,120 --> 01:36:08,590
You said to tell you
when I knew what I wanted.

1403
01:36:08,680 --> 01:36:10,636
I do.

1404
01:36:10,720 --> 01:36:13,109
It isn't Avigdor. It's no Longer a sin.

1405
01:36:13,200 --> 01:36:15,475
- H-Hadass, I...
- Shh.

1406
01:36:16,440 --> 01:36:20,479
It's been terrible for you, I know,
all this waiting.

1407
01:36:22,040 --> 01:36:24,315
But it's all right now.

1408
01:36:24,400 --> 01:36:26,960
You don't have to wait any Longer.

1409
01:36:28,360 --> 01:36:31,750
Oh, God! Oh, God! I'm so sorry.

1410
01:36:32,840 --> 01:36:35,559
- I'm so sorry, Hadass.
- For what?

1411
01:36:35,640 --> 01:36:38,677
For teaching me? For understanding me?

1412
01:36:38,760 --> 01:36:41,035
For making me fall in Love with you?

1413
01:36:42,240 --> 01:36:44,196
I can't! I can't!

1414
01:36:46,440 --> 01:36:48,954
I feel so certain that you Love me.

1415
01:36:50,080 --> 01:36:53,038
Everything you do
shows me you Love me.

1416
01:36:53,120 --> 01:36:55,156
What is it, Anshel?

1417
01:36:55,240 --> 01:36:58,198
* Look at how she looks at me

1418
01:36:58,880 --> 01:37:04,238
* But I can never look at her that way... *

1419
01:37:04,320 --> 01:37:06,709
Is it me? Am I so... ?

1420
01:37:07,560 --> 01:37:10,791
- Do you find me... ?
- I find you beautiful, beautiful.

1421
01:37:12,360 --> 01:37:14,510
Then what?

1422
01:37:14,600 --> 01:37:16,192
* Full of all the feelings

1423
01:37:16,280 --> 01:37:21,673
* And the soft unspoken words
that lovers say... *

1424
01:37:21,760 --> 01:37:24,672
There are things I wish I could explain,

1425
01:37:24,760 --> 01:37:27,115
things I'd Like to tell you.

1426
01:37:28,000 --> 01:37:29,752
I feel so...

1427
01:37:29,840 --> 01:37:33,674
- Maybe you’ll feel better tomorrow.
- I hope so.

1428
01:37:33,760 --> 01:37:35,716
* In all the words in all the books

1429
01:37:35,800 --> 01:37:38,758
* I wish there were a way to say

1430
01:37:38,840 --> 01:37:43,277
* What she's taught me
isn't written anywhere

1431
01:37:43,360 --> 01:37:48,115
* And I’m supposed to be
the one who's wise

1432
01:37:48,920 --> 01:37:50,512
* One thing is certain

1433
01:37:50,600 --> 01:37:53,876
* I can never be what she

1434
01:37:55,080 --> 01:37:59,039
* Expects of me

1435
01:38:08,200 --> 01:38:13,149
* I've wanted the shadows

1436
01:38:13,240 --> 01:38:16,596
* I don't any more

1437
01:38:17,800 --> 01:38:21,839
* No matter what happens

1438
01:38:21,920 --> 01:38:26,311
* I won't any more

1439
01:38:26,400 --> 01:38:30,154
* I've run from the sunlight

1440
01:38:30,240 --> 01:38:33,277
* Afraid it saw too much

1441
01:38:33,360 --> 01:38:37,558
* The moon had the one Light

1442
01:38:37,640 --> 01:38:40,029
* I bathed in

1443
01:38:40,120 --> 01:38:42,111
* I waked in

1444
01:38:42,200 --> 01:38:48,230
* I held in my feelings

1445
01:38:48,320 --> 01:38:51,232
* And closed every door

1446
01:38:52,200 --> 01:38:55,715
* No matter what happens

1447
01:38:55,800 --> 01:38:59,873
* I can't any more

1448
01:38:59,960 --> 01:39:03,919
* There's someone who must hear

1449
01:39:04,000 --> 01:39:07,913
* The words I've never spoken

1450
01:39:08,000 --> 01:39:11,629
* Tonight if he were here

1451
01:39:11,720 --> 01:39:15,838
* My silence would be broken

1452
01:39:15,920 --> 01:39:19,549
* I need him to touch me

1453
01:39:19,640 --> 01:39:22,552
* To know the Love that's in my heart

1454
01:39:22,640 --> 01:39:26,394
* The same heart that tells me

1455
01:39:26,480 --> 01:39:28,550
* To see myself

1456
01:39:28,640 --> 01:39:30,870
* To free myself

1457
01:39:30,960 --> 01:39:36,273
* To be myself at Last

1458
01:39:36,360 --> 01:39:41,195
* For too many mornings

1459
01:39:41,280 --> 01:39:44,829
* The curtains were drawn

1460
01:39:44,920 --> 01:39:48,196
* It's time they were opened

1461
01:39:48,280 --> 01:39:51,477
* To welcome the dawn

1462
01:39:51,560 --> 01:39:55,758
* A voice deep inside's getting stronger

1463
01:39:55,840 --> 01:40:00,277
* I can't keep it quiet any Longer

1464
01:40:00,360 --> 01:40:05,036
* No matter what happens

1465
01:40:05,120 --> 01:40:13,391
* It can't be the same any more

1466
01:40:22,360 --> 01:40:24,316
* I promise

1467
01:40:25,400 --> 01:40:27,630
* It won't be

1468
01:40:28,720 --> 01:40:32,076
* The same

1469
01:40:33,280 --> 01:40:39,116
* Any more *

1470
01:41:03,520 --> 01:41:05,078
I'll miss you.

1471
01:41:05,160 --> 01:41:07,515
You’ll have lots to do while I'm gone.

1472
01:41:07,600 --> 01:41:10,558
- I know, but...
- Tell your parents I'm sorry.

1473
01:41:10,640 --> 01:41:12,198
Sorry?

1474
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:14,635
That I wasn't here when they got home.

1475
01:41:14,720 --> 01:41:16,676
You’ll see them on Friday.

1476
01:41:16,760 --> 01:41:18,876
You can tell us about the city.

1477
01:41:18,960 --> 01:41:21,076
Show them the books you bought.

1478
01:41:23,480 --> 01:41:25,038
Oh...

1479
01:41:25,120 --> 01:41:27,076
I baked almond cakes.

1480
01:41:27,840 --> 01:41:31,276
You and Avigdor wouldn’t Last three days
without my almond cakes.

1481
01:41:31,360 --> 01:41:32,918
Thank you.

1482
01:41:36,880 --> 01:41:38,836
Hurry home.

1483
01:41:38,920 --> 01:41:41,718
It won't be the same here without you.

1484
01:41:41,800 --> 01:41:43,677
Hadass.

1485
01:41:43,760 --> 01:41:46,638
Do you remember
what we studied Last week

1486
01:41:46,720 --> 01:41:48,790
in the Talmud about patience?

1487
01:41:48,880 --> 01:41:51,348
Tell me, what did we read?

1488
01:41:51,440 --> 01:41:54,193
''Patience yields many good things. ''

1489
01:41:54,280 --> 01:41:57,636
If you have patience,
you’ll have everything you want.

1490
01:41:57,720 --> 01:42:00,553
Children, beautiful children,
as many as you want.

1491
01:42:01,640 --> 01:42:03,596
Trust me.

1492
01:42:04,840 --> 01:42:06,796
I do trust you.

1493
01:42:11,360 --> 01:42:14,557
Well, I... have to be going.

1494
01:42:20,960 --> 01:42:22,916
I'll study while you're away.

1495
01:42:23,640 --> 01:42:25,596
I want you to be proud of me.

1496
01:42:27,040 --> 01:42:29,270
Oh, I am proud of you.

1497
01:42:29,360 --> 01:42:31,590
You should be proud of yourself.

1498
01:42:34,440 --> 01:42:36,192
I Love you, Anshel.

1499
01:42:38,640 --> 01:42:40,596
I Love you too.

1500
01:42:50,440 --> 01:42:53,034
* She's mother

1501
01:42:53,120 --> 01:42:55,270
* She's sister

1502
01:42:55,360 --> 01:42:58,511
* She's lover

1503
01:42:58,600 --> 01:43:04,391
* She's the wonder of wonders

1504
01:43:04,480 --> 01:43:09,031
* No man can deny

1505
01:43:09,120 --> 01:43:13,989
* So why would he change her?

1506
01:43:14,080 --> 01:43:18,392
* She's loving, she's tender

1507
01:43:18,480 --> 01:43:23,349
* She's woman

1508
01:43:25,120 --> 01:43:31,639
* So am I *

1509
01:43:38,200 --> 01:43:40,350
This trip was a good idea, Anshel.

1510
01:43:40,440 --> 01:43:42,954
- I have a secret to tell you.
- Tell me.

1511
01:43:43,040 --> 01:43:45,793
- Not now.
- All right.

1512
01:43:45,880 --> 01:43:49,714
(Avigdor chuckles) So my crazy plan
was crazy after all.

1513
01:43:50,720 --> 01:43:52,073
What?

1514
01:43:52,160 --> 01:43:54,116
She Loves you now.

1515
01:43:54,200 --> 01:43:56,873
- She only thinks she does.
- What?

1516
01:43:58,120 --> 01:44:00,918
Things aren't always what they seem.

1517
01:44:01,000 --> 01:44:02,956
What are you talking about?

1518
01:44:03,040 --> 01:44:04,996
You’ll see.

1519
01:44:07,240 --> 01:44:09,595
Now, what's this secret of yours?

1520
01:44:12,080 --> 01:44:14,355
I'll tell you when we get to Lublin.

1521
01:44:17,920 --> 01:44:20,559
(Avigdor) Look, there's our friend again.

1522
01:44:20,640 --> 01:44:23,154
(Yentl) I wonder if it ever gets tired?

1523
01:44:36,280 --> 01:44:39,238
- When are you going to tell me?
- Not yet.

1524
01:44:39,320 --> 01:44:41,709
- Why not?
- I just can't.

1525
01:45:46,440 --> 01:45:48,351
Slivovitz?

1526
01:45:48,440 --> 01:45:50,192
No, thanks.

1527
01:45:51,280 --> 01:45:53,475
So let's hear the secret of yours.

1528
01:45:56,440 --> 01:45:58,590
Maybe I will have a glass.

1529
01:45:58,680 --> 01:46:01,035
Good. You look a little pale.

1530
01:46:05,120 --> 01:46:07,076
- Lechaim.
- Lechaim.

1531
01:46:15,560 --> 01:46:17,516
So tell me.

1532
01:46:22,440 --> 01:46:24,271
Well, er...

1533
01:46:26,400 --> 01:46:28,914
We're friends. What can't you tell me?

1534
01:46:32,000 --> 01:46:33,558
All right.

1535
01:46:36,400 --> 01:46:39,358
Avigdor, what would you do

1536
01:46:39,440 --> 01:46:43,319
if all you wanted in Life was to study
and it was forbidden?

1537
01:46:43,400 --> 01:46:45,960
- It isn't forbidden.
- What if it were?

1538
01:46:46,040 --> 01:46:50,272
What would you do if some crazy Law
said all men called Avigdor

1539
01:46:50,360 --> 01:46:53,272
or all men with brown eyes
were forbidden to study?

1540
01:46:53,360 --> 01:46:55,237
- I'd study anyway.
- Secretly?

1541
01:46:55,320 --> 01:46:57,072
If I had to. Why?

1542
01:46:57,160 --> 01:47:00,516
And that would be difficult,
always hiding, afraid?

1543
01:47:00,600 --> 01:47:02,591
Yes. What's your secret?

1544
01:47:02,680 --> 01:47:05,478
Without studying, you couldn’t Live.
Is that right?

1545
01:47:05,560 --> 01:47:08,233
- That's right.
- I couldn’t, either.

1546
01:47:08,320 --> 01:47:12,632
- So?
- So I studied, secretly.

1547
01:47:12,720 --> 01:47:16,190
No, you didn't.
What are you babbling about?

1548
01:47:18,680 --> 01:47:20,432
Avigdor...

1549
01:47:21,800 --> 01:47:23,756
my name isn't Anshel.

1550
01:47:24,640 --> 01:47:26,835
That's your secret?

1551
01:47:28,680 --> 01:47:30,671
Dear Avigdor.

1552
01:47:31,920 --> 01:47:35,708
- I don't know how to tell you this.
- Well, don't. I'll guess.

1553
01:47:35,800 --> 01:47:39,315
- I'm not a yeshiva boy.
- You're the chief rabbi of Lithuania.

1554
01:47:40,400 --> 01:47:44,598
- I'm not any kind of boy.
- Not the chief rabbi, all right.

1555
01:47:46,000 --> 01:47:47,752
My name isn't Anshel.

1556
01:47:48,600 --> 01:47:50,397
It's... it's Yentl.

1557
01:47:50,480 --> 01:47:51,833
Yentl?

1558
01:47:53,600 --> 01:47:55,431
And...

1559
01:47:58,960 --> 01:48:00,996
I'm a woman.

1560
01:48:02,040 --> 01:48:03,792
A woman.

1561
01:48:04,760 --> 01:48:06,716
A woman.

1562
01:48:07,440 --> 01:48:09,476
Now my secret.

1563
01:48:10,360 --> 01:48:13,158
- I'm the Tsar of Russia.
- Then I'll prove it.

1564
01:48:13,240 --> 01:48:17,119
- Stop this, Anshel.
- I'm not Anshel. I'm Yentl.

1565
01:48:19,520 --> 01:48:23,752
- I'm not a man. I'm a woman.
- Stop it.

1566
01:48:24,640 --> 01:48:27,871
- I'm a woman, Avigdor.
- Anshel, I don't Like this.

1567
01:48:27,960 --> 01:48:29,916
What kind of a game is this?

1568
01:48:30,000 --> 01:48:31,956
It's not a game.

1569
01:48:33,400 --> 01:48:35,356
Not any more.

1570
01:48:38,720 --> 01:48:40,995
What are you doing?

1571
01:48:45,920 --> 01:48:47,876
What are you doing?

1572
01:48:48,360 --> 01:48:50,430
(Avigdor sighs)

1573
01:48:58,360 --> 01:49:00,316
Oh, my God.

1574
01:49:01,320 --> 01:49:04,437
I've only shown you
so you can testify to the rabbis.

1575
01:49:04,520 --> 01:49:06,272
It can't be.

1576
01:49:06,360 --> 01:49:08,316
It is.

1577
01:49:09,760 --> 01:49:11,716
What have you done?

1578
01:49:12,640 --> 01:49:14,995
- Listen to me.
- Don't come near me.

1579
01:49:15,080 --> 01:49:17,640
- Let me explain.
- Don't touch me.

1580
01:49:17,720 --> 01:49:20,871
Avigdor, don't be afraid,
I'm not going to hurt you.

1581
01:49:20,960 --> 01:49:22,916
- You're a monster.
- No.

1582
01:49:23,000 --> 01:49:24,956
All I ever wanted to do was study.

1583
01:49:25,040 --> 01:49:28,396
''A woman shall not wear
that which pertained to a man. ''

1584
01:49:28,480 --> 01:49:30,596
- You're a devil.
- Try to understand...

1585
01:49:30,680 --> 01:49:33,069
- Enough! Please!
- I'm not a devil.

1586
01:49:33,160 --> 01:49:35,628
Every commandment broken, every day!

1587
01:49:35,720 --> 01:49:39,793
Stay away from me! Please!
What are you, a demon?

1588
01:49:39,880 --> 01:49:41,996
- I'm not.
- You spit on the Torah!

1589
01:49:42,080 --> 01:49:43,877
I Love the Torah!

1590
01:49:43,960 --> 01:49:47,032
You spit on it, on everything and everyone.

1591
01:49:47,120 --> 01:49:50,078
In God's face, my face, Hadass's face!

1592
01:49:50,160 --> 01:49:52,390
- God, Hadass!
- She knows nothing!

1593
01:49:52,480 --> 01:49:54,596
- Nothing?
- No, she's never...

1594
01:49:54,680 --> 01:49:57,911
An innocent married to a devil!
You married a woman!

1595
01:49:58,000 --> 01:50:00,275
- How could you do that?
- It was your idea!

1596
01:50:00,360 --> 01:50:02,635
- This? My doing?
- Yes!

1597
01:50:02,720 --> 01:50:07,874
Come on, you're a man. Answer me
Like a man. I want to know why. Why?

1598
01:50:07,960 --> 01:50:09,712
Why didn't you say you were a woman?

1599
01:50:09,800 --> 01:50:12,234
I was afraid of this, of exactly this!

1600
01:50:12,320 --> 01:50:15,232
So you lied to me, you lied to Hadass!

1601
01:50:15,320 --> 01:50:17,550
I told you things I wouldn’t tell a wife!

1602
01:50:17,640 --> 01:50:19,790
- I'm glad you told me.
- What kind of creature are you?

1603
01:50:19,880 --> 01:50:22,314
- Just a woman.
- I want the answer.

1604
01:50:22,400 --> 01:50:24,960
Tell me the answer. Why? Why?

1605
01:50:25,040 --> 01:50:27,508
- I... I was afraid.
- Why?

1606
01:50:27,600 --> 01:50:29,716
- I wanted to be near you.
- Why?

1607
01:50:29,800 --> 01:50:32,030
I didn't wanna Lose you. I Loved you.

1608
01:50:32,120 --> 01:50:34,873
(Sobbing)

1609
01:50:42,160 --> 01:50:44,469
(Avigdor) Oh, God.

1610
01:50:44,560 --> 01:50:47,393
Oh, God. Oh, my God.

1611
01:50:47,480 --> 01:50:49,436
(Sobbing) I Loved you.

1612
01:51:00,880 --> 01:51:03,872
I thought you didn't
understand about Love.

1613
01:51:06,200 --> 01:51:08,156
No wonder.

1614
01:51:09,120 --> 01:51:11,076
My God, no wonder.

1615
01:51:12,760 --> 01:51:16,753
All the times I looked at you and touched
you and I couldn’t understand why.

1616
01:51:16,840 --> 01:51:18,990
I thought something was wrong with me.

1617
01:51:19,080 --> 01:51:21,275
There was nothing wrong with you.

1618
01:51:21,360 --> 01:51:23,316
It was me.

1619
01:51:34,560 --> 01:51:36,516
Your skin.

1620
01:51:37,520 --> 01:51:39,272
It's so...

1621
01:51:41,440 --> 01:51:43,032
Your hair...

1622
01:51:43,120 --> 01:51:45,315
It must have been beautiful.

1623
01:51:46,160 --> 01:51:47,912
It’ll grow.

1624
01:51:49,200 --> 01:51:51,156
Your hands...

1625
01:51:52,000 --> 01:51:53,956
I always tried to hide them.

1626
01:51:54,040 --> 01:51:55,792
Oh, no.

1627
01:52:00,920 --> 01:52:02,876
I did... I...

1628
01:52:06,280 --> 01:52:08,236
I didn't want to touch you.

1629
01:52:11,240 --> 01:52:12,798
I was afraid to.

1630
01:52:20,120 --> 01:52:21,951
Your mouth...

1631
01:52:28,240 --> 01:52:29,992
Yentl.

1632
01:52:32,680 --> 01:52:34,636
I Loved you too.

1633
01:53:00,360 --> 01:53:02,112
Hadass.

1634
01:53:12,360 --> 01:53:14,316
It's not...

1635
01:53:15,800 --> 01:53:17,552
difficult.

1636
01:53:18,920 --> 01:53:21,275
I'll write a statement to the rabbis

1637
01:53:22,840 --> 01:53:25,513
that the marriage was never consummated.

1638
01:53:25,600 --> 01:53:29,149
You can take it back to Beshev,
give it to the rabbis.

1639
01:53:29,240 --> 01:53:31,196
The rabbis witnessed it.

1640
01:53:31,280 --> 01:53:35,751
Witnessed what, a marriage between
two women? It's null and void.

1641
01:53:35,840 --> 01:53:38,195
According to divorce procedures...

1642
01:53:38,280 --> 01:53:42,592
No, according to God,
it was not a marriage.

1643
01:53:42,680 --> 01:53:45,831
This is crazy.
I'm arguing Talmud with a woman.

1644
01:53:51,560 --> 01:53:53,516
It's not the first time.

1645
01:54:04,680 --> 01:54:06,636
Go back to her, Avigdor.

1646
01:54:09,920 --> 01:54:13,799
I don't think Hadass will Listen
to her parents any more.

1647
01:54:13,880 --> 01:54:18,431
Maybe there's something we can do,
a Law or something...

1648
01:54:18,520 --> 01:54:20,875
Avigdor, there's no book with this in it.

1649
01:54:22,840 --> 01:54:26,469
Sometimes... right can come from wrong,

1650
01:54:27,840 --> 01:54:29,592
virtue from sin.

1651
01:54:29,680 --> 01:54:31,989
It's in the Talmud somewhere.

1652
01:54:33,480 --> 01:54:35,232
We’ll go to another town.

1653
01:54:35,320 --> 01:54:37,834
We’ll get married, have children.

1654
01:54:37,920 --> 01:54:39,990
We’ll find a new yeshiva.

1655
01:54:40,080 --> 01:54:41,718
For both of us?

1656
01:54:42,680 --> 01:54:44,636
You still want to study?

1657
01:54:45,680 --> 01:54:49,992
We've argued the Bible back to Genesis,
chapter one, verse one.

1658
01:54:50,080 --> 01:54:52,150
How could you still ask me that question?

1659
01:54:52,240 --> 01:54:54,629
You don't need to any more.

1660
01:54:54,720 --> 01:54:57,109
I'll do the thinking, I'll handle everything.

1661
01:54:57,200 --> 01:54:59,873
I want to study with you, not darn socks.

1662
01:54:59,960 --> 01:55:02,599
- Impossible.
- Nothing's impossible.

1663
01:55:02,680 --> 01:55:05,638
You can study at home.
No one has to know.

1664
01:55:05,720 --> 01:55:08,996
And draw the curtains,
close the shutters?

1665
01:55:09,080 --> 01:55:11,958
- I want you to be a real woman.
- I am.

1666
01:55:12,040 --> 01:55:13,792
Then act Like one!

1667
01:55:13,880 --> 01:55:17,350
There's no gift from God
more beautiful and miraculous.

1668
01:55:17,440 --> 01:55:20,318
You know everything
without opening books.

1669
01:55:20,400 --> 01:55:22,356
What more do you want?

1670
01:55:26,400 --> 01:55:27,992
More.

1671
01:56:02,840 --> 01:56:05,479
Your beard.

1672
01:56:05,560 --> 01:56:08,199
I suppose it’ll never grow in now.

1673
01:56:13,240 --> 01:56:15,196
How could I have been so blind?

1674
01:56:18,120 --> 01:56:20,759
Here's a statement for the rabbi

1675
01:56:20,840 --> 01:56:22,796
and a note for Hadass.

1676
01:56:23,440 --> 01:56:25,908
Would you give it to her for me, please?

1677
01:56:26,840 --> 01:56:28,592
I'll miss you.

1678
01:56:29,680 --> 01:56:31,875
I'll miss you too, Avigdor.

1679
01:56:55,160 --> 01:56:57,196
Goodbye, Anshel.

1680
01:56:58,520 --> 01:57:00,556
Yentl.

1681
01:57:04,120 --> 01:57:05,473
Yentl.

1682
01:57:16,040 --> 01:57:17,996
* There are moments

1683
01:57:19,240 --> 01:57:22,038
* You remember all your Life

1684
01:57:22,920 --> 01:57:25,832
* There are moments you know

1685
01:57:25,920 --> 01:57:29,879
* Will be with you all your Life

1686
01:57:31,360 --> 01:57:34,238
* His face

1687
01:57:34,320 --> 01:57:39,348
* Will be written on my mind

1688
01:57:40,440 --> 01:57:46,390
* Will be written in my heart

1689
01:57:48,160 --> 01:57:55,032
* As Long as I Live *

1690
01:57:56,160 --> 01:57:58,390
My dear Avigdor.

1691
01:57:58,480 --> 01:58:01,756
After many months,
your letter finally reached me.

1692
01:58:01,840 --> 01:58:03,796
I hope this one finds you!

1693
01:58:03,880 --> 01:58:05,791
Since we said goodbye,

1694
01:58:05,880 --> 01:58:09,395
I’ve prayed that,
despite the pain I’ve caused,

1695
01:58:09,480 --> 01:58:12,153
some happiness would come out of it.

1696
01:58:13,000 --> 01:58:15,230
And now you tell me it has.

1697
01:58:15,320 --> 01:58:18,437
As for me, I’m going to a new place

1698
01:58:18,520 --> 01:58:21,080
where I hear things are different.

1699
01:58:21,160 --> 01:58:23,469
Anyway, we'll see.

1700
01:58:23,560 --> 01:58:26,313
Take care of yourself, and Hadass.

1701
01:58:26,400 --> 01:58:29,073
l hope she continues with her studies.

1702
01:58:29,160 --> 01:58:31,435
She has great promise.

1703
01:58:31,520 --> 01:58:35,399
And remember,
l will love you both, always.

1704
01:58:37,080 --> 01:58:42,837
* Tell me where

1705
01:58:44,440 --> 01:58:49,468
* Where is it written
what it is I’m meant to be?

1706
01:58:58,520 --> 01:59:01,671
* That I can't dare?

1707
01:59:08,280 --> 01:59:11,955
* It all began

1708
01:59:13,600 --> 01:59:16,319
* The day I found

1709
01:59:17,480 --> 01:59:24,716
* That from my window
I could only see a piece of sky

1710
01:59:24,800 --> 01:59:27,678
* I stepped outside

1711
01:59:28,400 --> 01:59:31,517
* And looked around

1712
01:59:32,320 --> 01:59:36,233
* I never dreamed it was so wide

1713
01:59:36,840 --> 01:59:39,752
* Or even half as high

1714
01:59:39,840 --> 01:59:42,149
* The time had come

1715
01:59:42,240 --> 01:59:44,196
* Papa, can you hear me?

1716
01:59:44,280 --> 01:59:45,759
* To try my wings

1717
01:59:45,840 --> 01:59:48,070
* Papa, are you near me?

1718
01:59:48,160 --> 01:59:52,631
* And even though
it seemed at any moment

1719
01:59:52,720 --> 01:59:54,597
* I could fall

1720
01:59:54,680 --> 01:59:57,035
* I felt the most...

1721
01:59:57,120 --> 01:59:59,190
* Papa, can you see me?

1722
01:59:59,280 --> 02:00:02,716
*. . amazing things
Can you understand me?

1723
02:00:02,800 --> 02:00:05,758
* The things you can't imagine

1724
02:00:05,840 --> 02:00:09,310
* If you've never flown at all

1725
02:00:09,400 --> 02:00:13,188
* Though it's safer to stay on the ground

1726
02:00:13,280 --> 02:00:16,352
* Sometimes where danger Lies

1727
02:00:16,440 --> 02:00:20,353
* There the sweetest of pleasures
are found

1728
02:00:20,440 --> 02:00:23,637
* No matter where I go

1729
02:00:23,720 --> 02:00:28,350
* There'll be memories
that tug at my sieve

1730
02:00:28,440 --> 02:00:31,671
* But there will also be

1731
02:00:31,760 --> 02:00:36,072
* More to question, yet more to believe

1732
02:00:36,160 --> 02:00:41,029
* Oh, tell me where

1733
02:00:41,120 --> 02:00:46,069
* Where is the someone
who will turn to look at me?

1734
02:00:46,160 --> 02:00:50,233
* And want to share

1735
02:00:50,320 --> 02:00:56,156
* My every sweet imagined possibility?

1736
02:00:58,160 --> 02:01:01,391
* The more I live

1737
02:01:02,640 --> 02:01:06,155
* The more I Learn

1738
02:01:06,240 --> 02:01:10,836
* The more I Learn, the more I realize

1739
02:01:10,920 --> 02:01:13,514
* The less I know

1740
02:01:13,600 --> 02:01:15,477
* Each step I take

1741
02:01:15,560 --> 02:01:17,312
* Papa, I've a voice now

1742
02:01:17,400 --> 02:01:18,958
* Each page I turn

1743
02:01:19,040 --> 02:01:20,996
* Papa, I've a choice now

1744
02:01:21,080 --> 02:01:24,038
* Each mile I travel only means

1745
02:01:24,120 --> 02:01:27,510
* The more I have to go

1746
02:01:27,600 --> 02:01:31,115
* What's wrong with wanting more?

1747
02:01:31,200 --> 02:01:35,352
* If you can fly, then soar

1748
02:01:35,440 --> 02:01:38,637
* With all there is

1749
02:01:38,720 --> 02:01:44,829
* Why settle for...

1750
02:01:44,920 --> 02:01:53,635
* Just a piece of sky?

1751
02:01:53,720 --> 02:01:57,190
* Papa, I can hear you

1752
02:01:57,280 --> 02:01:59,953
* Papa, I can see you

1753
02:02:00,040 --> 02:02:03,953
* Papa, I can feel you

1754
02:02:04,040 --> 02:02:06,076
* Papa

1755
02:02:06,160 --> 02:02:08,674
* Watch me

1756
02:02:08,760 --> 02:02:27,669
* Fly *
Vtg

